100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On January 13, 1926, the League of Nations continued its efforts to promote global cooperation, with discussions focusing on disarmament and the ongoing tensions in the Far East. In the United States, a severe cold wave gripped the Midwest, leading to widespread disruptions and prompting warnings from local authorities. Meanwhile, in the realm of entertainment, the film industry buzzed with the anticipated release of "The Son of the Sheik," starring Rudolph Valentino, promising to captivate audiences across the nation.
